{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871362239,"sessionID":"ses_285d27a16ffe0wLYGNrj8mZFua","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2d956b001V4IZuRr0g3Zq2U","messageID":"msg_d7a2d86d1001sFioR1BF7tTQkg","sessionID":"ses_285d27a16ffe0wLYGNrj8mZFua","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"toolu_ec4528592e144049b0d4341a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project in the current workspace. I need to understand:\n1. The overall project structure\n2. Any existing spec files (*.md that might be specs)\n3. Any existing Helm charts or Kubernetes manifests\n4. The manifests module structure\n\nPlease provide a summary of the project structure, especially focusing on any manifests/helm-related directories.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_285d26299ffeg5qVJKp4oCz5Ih (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nBased on my exploration, here is a comprehensive summary of the agentcube project:\n\n---\n\n## AgentCube Project Summary\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\nThe project is a **Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents** with the following top-level directories:\n\n| Directory | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/` | Python SDK/CLI module |\n| `cmd/` | Go binaries (agentd, picod, router, workload-manager) |\n| `pkg/` | Go packages (apis, client, common, router, store, workloadmanager, picod, agentd) |\n| `deployment/` | Deployment specifications (design.md, spec.md, client-go.md) |\n| `testing/` | Test specifications (agentcube_tdd_manifest.md) |\n| `changes/` | Change requests (AR-001 through AR-030) with delta-specs and tasks |\n| `python-sdk/` | Python SDK design/specs |\n| `cli-toolkit/` | CLI toolkit design/specs |\n| `session-store/` | Session store design/specs |\n| `session-routing/` | Session routing design/specs |\n| `sandbox-orchestration/` | Sandbox orchestration design/specs |\n| `idle-cleanup/` | Idle cleanup design/specs |\n| `code-execution/` | Code execution design/specs |\n| `integrations/` | Integrations design/specs |\n| `ci-cd/` | CI/CD design/specs |\n\n### 2. Spec Files (*.md)\n\n**Root-level specs:**\n- `project.md` - Project context and architecture\n- `design.md` - Main design document\n- `delta-spec.md` - Delta specification\n- `proposal.md` - Project proposal\n- `tasks.md` - Main tasks\n- `test_spec.md` - Test specification\n\n**Module-level specs** exist in each module directory (design.md, spec.md).\n\n**Testing manifest:**\n- `testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md` - TDD manifest defining test contracts for all core components\n\n### 3. Helm Charts and Kubernetes Manifests\n\n**Current Status: NO HELM CHARTS OR KUBERNETES MANIFESTS EXIST YET**\n\nHowever, the **deployment/spec.md** explicitly defines the requirements for:\n- Helm chart location: `manifests/charts/base`\n- CRD definitions: `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` and `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n- Required templates for WorkloadManager, Router, RBAC, and optional Volcano scheduler\n\nThe **changes/AR-030** proposal contains detailed tasks for creating the Helm chart:\n- Chart.yaml and values.yaml\n- Templates for WorkloadManager (Deployment + Service)\n- Templates for Router (Deployment + Service)\n- RBAC templates\n- CRD manifests\n\n### 4. AgentCube Python Module Structure\n\nThe `agentcube/` directory contains:\n```\nagentcube/\n  __init__.py\n  agent_runtime.py      - Agent runtime implementation\n  code_interpreter.py   - Code interpreter\n  exceptions.py         - Exception definitions\n  cli/                  - CLI implementation\n  clients/              - Client implementations (control plane, data plane)\n  models/               - Data models\n  operations/           - Operations\n  runtime/              - Runtime (build, invoke, pack, publish, status)\n  services/             - Services (agentcube provider, docker, k8s, metadata)\n  utils/                - Utilities (http, log, utils)\n```\n\n### Key Findings\n\n1. **No manifests directory exists** - The project has specs defining what the Helm chart should contain, but the actual `manifests/charts/base/` directory has not been created yet.\n\n2. **CRDs defined in code** - The Kubernetes CRDs are defined in Go at `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` and need to be generated as YAML manifests.\n\n3. **The testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md** is the closest thing to a \"manifests module\" - it defines the test contract for the entire system.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_285d26299ffeg5qVJKp4oCz5Ih","model":{"modelID":"MiniMax-M2.5","providerID":"bailian-coding-plan"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775871303011,"end":1775871362236}}}}
