{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871462372,"sessionID":"ses_285d27a16ffe0wLYGNrj8mZFua","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2ef7e90015d127e2465R1CE","messageID":"msg_d7a2ee016001APUl0alYmcTRdI","sessionID":"ses_285d27a16ffe0wLYGNrj8mZFua","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_98d71152a7d942dd99a933dc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Helm Chart templates and values configuration for deploying AgentCube to Kubernetes, providing a reusable, configurable deployment mechanism for the Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, and associated RBAC resources.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-030\n- **Module**: `manifests`\n- **Language**: YAML\n- **Size**: L\n- **Base Specs**: `deployment/spec.md`, `deployment/design.md`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nAgentCube requires a standardized deployment mechanism to Kubernetes clusters. The deployment/spec.md document defines the expected chart structure, but the actual template files need implementation. The Helm chart enables reproducible deployments, configuration management via values.yaml, namespace-scoped installations, optional components (RBAC, Volcano scheduler), and CRD lifecycle management.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-030-001: Chart 结构与元数据\n\nThe Helm chart SHALL provide proper structure and metadata for Helm 3 compatibility.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-001-A — Chart.yaml 包含正确的元数据\n\n- **GIVEN** a chart directory at `manifests/charts/base/`\n- **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL pass without errors\n- **AND** the chart SHALL have `name: agentcube` and `version: 0.1.0` in Chart.yaml\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-001-B — values.yaml 包含所有必需配置项\n\n- **GIVEN** the `values.yaml` file exists in the chart\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain keys for `redis.addr`, `redis.password`, `workloadmanager.*`, `router.*`, and `volcano.scheduler.*`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-001-C — 目录结构完整\n\n- **GIVEN** the chart directory structure exists\n- **WHEN** the chart is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain: `Chart.yaml`, `values.yaml`, `templates/`, and `crds/`\n\n---\n\n### AR-030-002: Helm 安装与 Namespace 管理\n\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-002-A — Helm install 创建 namespace\n\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **AND** `redis.addr` is set to a valid Redis address in values\n- **WHEN** `helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube --create-namespace` is executed\n- **THEN** the namespace `agentcube` SHALL be created\n- **AND** all resources SHALL be deployed to that namespace\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-002-B — Helm upgrade 成功渲染模板\n\n- **GIVEN** the chart is already installed\n- **AND** values are provided with required `redis.addr`\n- **WHEN** `helm upgrade agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL succeed without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n---\n\n### AR-030-003: Redis 环境变量注入\n\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password`.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-003-A — Workload Manager 接收 Redis 配置\n\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis-master:6379` and `redis.password: secret123` are set in values\n- **WHEN** the Workload Manager pod starts\n- **THEN** the container SHALL have `REDIS_ADDR=redis-master:6379` environment variable\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD=secret123` environment variable\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-003-B — Router 接收 Redis 配置\n\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis-master:6379` is set in values\n- **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n- **THEN** the container SHALL have `REDIS_ADDR=redis-master:6379` environment variable\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` from values (empty string if not set)\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-003-C — Redis 密码可为空\n\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis:6379` is set and `redis.password` is omitted or empty\n- **WHEN** pods start\n- **THEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` SHALL be set to empty string `\"\"`\n\n---\n\n### AR-030-004: Workload Manager Deployment 配置\n\nThe system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with configurable replica count, image, service type, resources, health probes, and environment variables.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-004-A — 默认副本数\n\n- **GIVEN** default chart values\n- **WHEN** the chart is installed\n- **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL have `replicas: 1`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-004-B — 自定义副本数\n\n- **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.replicas: 3` in values\n- **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n- **THEN** the Deployment SHALL have `replicas: 3`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-004-C — 容器镜像可配置\n\n- **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.image.repository: my-registry/workloadmanager` and `image.tag: v1.0.0` in values\n- **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** the container image SHALL be `my-registry/workloadmanager:v1.0.0`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-004-D — Service 端口配置\n\n- **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.service.port: 9090` in values\n- **WHEN** the Service is rendered\n- **THEN** it SHALL expose port `9090`\n- **AND** targetPort SHALL match the container port\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-004-E — 健康检查探针\n\n- **GIVEN** default chart values\n- **WHEN** the Workload Manager pod is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL have a livenessProbe HTTP GET on `/health`\n- **AND** a readinessProbe HTTP GET on `/health`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-004-F — 资源限制可配置\n\n- **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: \"2\"` and `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: \"2Gi\"` in values\n- **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** the container SHALL have those resource limits\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-004-G — 额外环境变量\n\n- **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.extraEnv: [{\"name\": \"CUSTOM_VAR\", \"value\": \"custom-value\"}]` in values\n- **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** the container SHALL include `CUSTOM_VAR` environment variable\n\n---\n\n### AR-030-005: Router Deployment 配置\n\nThe system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, ClusterIP service, resources, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing to the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-005-A — Router 默认副本数\n\n- **GIVEN** default chart values\n- **WHEN** the chart is installed\n- **THEN** the Router `Deployment` SHALL have `replicas: 1`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-005-B — Router 连接到 Workload Manager\n\n- **GIVEN** release namespace `agentcube` and Workload Manager service port `8080`\n- **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:8080`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-005-C — Router 镜像可配置\n\n- **GIVEN** `router.image.repository: my-registry/agentcube-router` and `image.tag: latest` in values\n- **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** the container image SHALL be `my-registry/agentcube-router:latest`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-005-D — Router Service 类型可配置\n\n- **GIVEN** `router.service.type: LoadBalancer` in values\n- **WHEN** the Service is rendered\n- **THEN** it SHALL have `type: LoadBalancer`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-005-E — Router 健康检查\n\n- **GIVEN** default chart values\n- **WHEN** the Router pod is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL have livenessProbe on `/health/live`\n- **AND** readinessProbe on `/health/ready`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-005-F — Router 资源限制\n\n- **GIVEN** `router.resources.limits.cpu: \"1\"` and `router.resources.limits.memory: \"1Gi\"` in values\n- **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** the container SHALL have those resource limits\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-005-G — Router 调试模式\n\n- **GIVEN** `router.debug: true` in values\n- **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** the container args SHALL include `--debug`\n\n---\n\n### AR-030-006: Workload Manager RBAC\n\nThe system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the required permissions for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-006-A — ServiceAccount 创建\n\n- **GIVEN** chart installation\n- **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n- **THEN** a `ServiceAccount` named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created in the release namespace\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-006-B — ClusterRole 权限\n\n- **GIVEN** the chart is installed\n- **WHEN** the ClusterRole is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n  - `sandboxes` (CRD) - all verbs\n  - `sandboxclaims` (CRD) - all verbs\n  - `codeinterpreters` (CRD) - all verbs\n  - `agentruntimes` (CRD) - all verbs\n  - `pods` (core) - list, watch, delete\n  - `secrets` (core) - get, list, watch, create, update, delete\n  - `tokenreviews` (authentication.k8s.io) - create\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-006-C — ClusterRoleBinding 绑定\n\n- **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n- **THEN** `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager` SHALL bind `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `agentcube` to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager`\n\n---\n\n### AR-030-007: Router 命名空间 RBAC (可选)\n\nThe system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-007-A — RBAC 默认禁用\n\n- **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false` (default)\n- **WHEN** templates render\n- **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-007-B — RBAC 启用时创建\n\n- **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` in values\n- **AND** `router.serviceAccountName: agentcube-router` (or defaulted)\n- **WHEN** the chart is applied\n- **THEN** a `ServiceAccount` named `agentcube-router` SHALL be created\n- **AND** a `Role` granting secrets verbs SHALL be created in the release namespace\n- **AND** a `RoleBinding` SHALL bind the ServiceAccount to the Role\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-007-C — Router 使用专用 ServiceAccount\n\n- **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName: custom-router-sa` in values\n- **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** the Router Deployment SHALL use `serviceAccountName: custom-router-sa`\n\n---\n\n### AR-030-008: Volcano Agent Scheduler (可选)\n\nThe system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-008-A — 默认不启用\n\n- **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n- **WHEN** templates render\n- **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-008-B — 启用时创建资源\n\n- **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true` in values\n- **WHEN** the chart is applied\n- **THEN** it SHALL create:\n  - `ServiceAccount` for the scheduler\n  - `ConfigMap` with agent-scheduler configuration\n  - `ClusterRole` with Volcano scheduling permissions\n  - `ClusterRoleBinding` for the scheduler\n  - `Service` for the scheduler\n  - `Deployment` for the scheduler\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-008-C — Volcano 镜像可配置\n\n- **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.image.repository: custom-volcano/agent-scheduler` in values\n- **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** the container image SHALL use that repository\n\n---\n\n### AR-030-009: CRD 清单\n\nThe system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` in the chart's `crds/` directory.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-009-A — CRD 目录存在\n\n- **GIVEN** the chart exists\n- **WHEN** the chart is inspected\n- **THEN** a `crds/` directory SHALL exist with CRD YAML files\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-009-B — AgentRuntime CRD\n\n- **GIVEN** the CRD manifests are present\n- **WHEN** the `agentruntimes` CRD is applied\n- **THEN** it SHALL have API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n- **AND** version `v1alpha1`\n- **AND** `scope: Namespaced`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-009-C — CodeInterpreter CRD\n\n- **GIVEN** the CRD manifests are present\n- **WHEN** the `codeinterpreters` CRD is applied\n- **THEN** it SHALL have API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n- **AND** version `v1alpha1`\n- **AND** `scope: Namespaced`\n\n---\n\n### AR-030-010: Helm 模板验证\n\nThe chart SHALL pass Helm validation and render correctly.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-010-A — Helm lint 通过\n\n- **GIVEN** the chart at `manifests/charts/base/`\n- **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL exit with code 0 (success)\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-010-B — 模板渲染无错误\n\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis:6379` is provided\n- **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL render without errors\n- **AND** produce valid Kubernetes YAML\n\n#### Scenario: AR-030-010-C — 完整渲染包含所有资源\n\n- **GIVEN** all required values are provided\n- **AND** `router.rbac.create: true` and `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`\n- **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n- **THEN** output SHALL include:\n  - WorkloadManager Deployment and Service\n  - Router Deployment and Service\n  - WorkloadManager RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n  - Router RBAC (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding)\n  - Volcano scheduler resources\n  - CRDs installed via `crds/` directory\n\n---\n\n## Non-Requirements\n\nThe following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n\n- Kubernetes cluster provisioning\n- Ingress configuration\n- Prometheus/Grafana monitoring stack\n- Redis deployment (external dependency)\n- Application-level secrets management beyond RBAC\n- Multi-cluster deployment strategies\n- Helm hook-based upgrade migrations\n- Custom Ingress or NetworkPolicy configurations\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Description |\n|------------|-------------|\n| deployment/spec.md | Base deployment requirements |\n| deployment/design.md | Helm chart specification |\n| pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ | CRD type definitions (source for generated CRDs) |\n| Helm 3 | Chart rendering and installation |\n| Kubernetes 1.19+ | API versions used |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n|----|-----------|---------------------|\n| AC030-001 | Chart.yaml renders with name=agentcube, version=0.1.0 | `helm lint` |\n| AC030-002 | values.yaml contains all documented keys with correct defaults | YAML parsing |\n| AC030-003 | Helm install creates namespace | `kubectl get ns` |\n| AC030-004 | Workload Manager receives REDIS_ADDR and REDIS_PASSWORD env vars | Pod inspection |\n| AC030-005 | Router receives REDIS_ADDR and REDIS_PASSWORD env vars | Pod inspection |\n| AC030-006 | Workload Manager Deployment has configurable replicas | `helm template` inspection |\n| AC030-007 | Workload Manager Service exposes correct port | Service YAML inspection |\n| AC030-008 | Router has WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL pointing to Workload Manager | Pod env inspection |\n| AC030-009 | RBAC ClusterRole contains required permissions | ClusterRole YAML inspection |\n| AC030-010 | Optional router RBAC renders only when enabled | Conditional rendering test |\n| AC030-011 | Optional Volcano scheduler renders only when enabled | Conditional rendering test |\n| AC030-012 | CRDs present in crds/ directory | Directory inspection |\n| AC030-013 | Helm template renders without error | `helm template` exit code |\n| AC030-014 | Helm lint passes | `helm lint` exit code |\n\n---\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n- Validate Chart.yaml and values.yaml structure\n- Test conditional rendering logic in templates\n- Verify RBAC rule completeness\n- Verify environment variable injection\n\n### Integration Tests\n- Test `helm install` and `helm upgrade` in a kind cluster\n- Verify all resources are created correctly\n- Test optional component toggles\n- Validate RBAC bindings\n\n### Template Validation\n- Use `helm template` for rendering tests\n- Use `helm lint` for schema validation\n- Use `helm diff` for upgrade path testing","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871462348,"end":1775871462368}}}}
